Data
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ HasRole
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the account has been granted the role
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the account has not been granted the role
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return false
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the role has never been granted to any account
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return false
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the account is the zero address
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return false
в””в”Ђв”Ђ RequireRole
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the account has the role
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should not revert
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the account does not have the role
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with {AccessControlUnauthorizedAccount}

Admin
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ GetRoleAdmin
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the role has never had an explicit admin set
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the default admin role
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the role has an explicit admin set
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the stored admin role
в””в”Ђв”Ђ SetRoleAdmin
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the caller has the current admin role for the target role
    в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should update the admin role mapping
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit a {RoleAdminChanged} event
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the caller does not have the current admin role for the target role
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with {AccessControlUnauthorizedAccount}

Grant
в””в”Ђв”Ђ GrantRole
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the caller has the admin role for the target role
    в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ and the account does not yet have the role
    в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should set hasRole[account][role] to true
    в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should emit a {RoleGranted} event
    в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true from the module function
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ and the account already has the role
    в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should leave hasRole[account][role] unchanged
    в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should not emit an additional {RoleGranted} event
    в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return false from the module function
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the caller does not have the admin role for the target role
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with {AccessControlUnauthorizedAccount}

Revoke
в””в”Ђв”Ђ RevokeRole
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the caller has the admin role for the target role
    в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ and the account currently has the role
    в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should set hasRole[account][role] to false
    в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should emit a {RoleRevoked} event
    в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true from the module function
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ and the account does not have the role
    в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should leave hasRole[account][role] unchanged
    в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return false from the module function
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the caller does not have the admin role for the target role
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with {AccessControlUnauthorizedAccount}

Renounce
в””в”Ђв”Ђ RenounceRole
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when msg.sender equals the account
    в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ and the account currently has the role
    в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should set hasRole[account][role] to false
    в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit a {RoleRevoked} event
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ and the account does not have the role
    в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should be a no-op and not emit any event
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when msg.sender does not equal the account
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with {AccessControlUnauthorizedSender}

Batch
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Grant
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ GrantRoleBatch
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the caller has the admin role for the target role
в”‚       в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ and the accounts array is empty
в”‚       в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should succeed without emitting any events
в”‚       в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ and the accounts array is non-empty
в”‚       в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ for each account without the role
в”‚       в”‚       в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should set hasRole[account][role] to true
в”‚       в”‚       в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit a {RoleGranted} event
в”‚       в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ for each account that already has the role
в”‚       в”‚           в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should not change storage or emit {RoleGranted}
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the caller does not have the admin role for the target role
в”‚           в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with {AccessControlUnauthorizedAccount}
в””в”Ђв”Ђ Revoke
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ RevokeRoleBatch
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the caller has the admin role for the target role
        в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ and the accounts array is empty
        в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should succeed without emitting any events
        в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ and the accounts array is non-empty
        в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ for each account with the role
        в”‚       в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should set hasRole[account][role] to false
        в”‚       в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit a {RoleRevoked} event
        в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ for each account that does not have the role
        в”‚           в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should not change storage or emit {RoleRevoked}
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the caller does not have the admin role for the target role
            в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with {AccessControlUnauthorizedAccount}

RoleHierarchy
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when a roleвЂ™s admin role is itself
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ an account with the role should be able to grant and revoke that same role
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when roles form a linear hierarchy (role1 admin is DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE, role2 admin is role1, role3 admin is role2)
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ only DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE holders can grant role1
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ only role1 holders can grant role2
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ only role2 holders can grant role3
в””в”Ђв”Ђ when roles form a circular admin relationship
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ each grant or revoke must still satisfy the immediate admin-role check

Pausable
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ IsRolePaused
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the role has not been paused
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return false
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the role has been paused
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ PauseRole
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the caller has the admin role for the target role
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should set pausedRoles[role] to true
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit a {RolePaused} event
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the caller does not have the admin role for the target role
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ on the facet surface it should revert with {AccessControlUnauthorizedAccount}
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ on the module surface it should follow the current split implementation semantics
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ UnpauseRole
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the caller has the admin role for the target role
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should set pausedRoles[role] to false
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit a {RoleUnpaused} event
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the caller does not have the admin role for the target role
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ on the facet surface it should revert with {AccessControlUnauthorizedAccount}
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ on the module surface it should follow the current split implementation semantics
в””в”Ђв”Ђ RequireRoleNotPaused
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the account does not have the role
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with {AccessControlUnauthorizedAccount}
    в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the account has the role and the role is paused
    в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with {AccessControlRolePaused}
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the account has the role and the role is not paused
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should not revert

Temporal
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Data
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ GetRoleExpiry
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when no expiry has been set for the role assignment
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return 0
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when an expiry has been set for the role assignment
в”‚   в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return the stored expiry timestamp
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ IsRoleExpired
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when no expiry is set and the account does not have the role
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when no expiry is set and the account has the role
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return false
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when an expiry is set in the future
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return false
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ when block.timestamp is greater than or equal to the stored expiry
в”‚   в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should return true
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ RequireValidRole
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the account does not have the role
в”‚       в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with {AccessControlUnauthorizedAccount}
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the account has the role and no expiry is set
в”‚       в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should not revert
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the account has the role and the expiry is in the future
в”‚       в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should not revert
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the account has the role and block.timestamp is greater than or equal to the stored expiry
в”‚           в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with {AccessControlRoleExpired}
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ Grant
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ GrantRoleWithExpiry
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the caller has the admin role for the target role
в”‚       в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ and the expiry is in the future
в”‚       в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should grant the role if it is not already granted
в”‚       в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should set the expiry timestamp
в”‚       в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit a {RoleGrantedWithExpiry} event
в”‚       в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ and the expiry is less than or equal to block.timestamp
в”‚       в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with {AccessControlRoleExpired}
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the caller does not have the admin role for the target role
в”‚           в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with {AccessControlUnauthorizedAccount}
в””в”Ђв”Ђ Revoke
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ RevokeTemporalRole
        в”њв”Ђв”Ђ when the caller has the admin role for the target role
        в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ and the account currently has the role
        в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should set hasRole[account][role] to false
        в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ it should clear the expiry timestamp
        в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should emit a {TemporalRoleRevoked} event
        в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ and the account does not have the role
        в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should be a no-op
        в””в”Ђв”Ђ when the caller does not have the admin role for the target role
            в””в”Ђв”Ђ it should revert with {AccessControlUnauthorizedAccount}

